sys_hub_action_type_definition.description:
Create a fixed asset in SAP ECC – RFC.

Inputs :

  • Connection Alias - Connection alias for SAP ECC - RFC.
  • Company Code - Legal entity for balance sheet and profit & loss statements.
  • Reference Asset For Creating - Complex object containing these fields:
    • Company Code
    • Asset
    • Subnumber
  • General Data - Complex object containing these fields:
    • Asset class
    • Description
    • Additional description
    • Acct determination
    • Serial number
    • Inventory number
    • Quantity
    • Base Unit of Measure
    • Base unit ISO code
    • Manage historically
    • Asset main no. text
  • Depreciation Areas - Objects containing these fields:
    • Depreciation area
    • Short name dep.area
    • Dep.area deactivated
    • Depreciation key
    • Useful life
    • Usef.life in periods
    • Expired useful life
    • Expired UL periods
    • Exp.spec.dep. life
    • Exp.UL periods SDep.
    • Original useful life
    • Orig.life in periods
    • Changeover year
    • No. of units deprec.
    • Ordinary deprec.
    • Special depreciation
    • Interest calculation
    • Operating readiness
    • Index series
    • Age-dependent index
    • Variable dep.portion
    • Scrap value
    • Currency
    • ISO code currency
    • Negative values allowed
    • Group asset
    • Sub-number
    • Acquis.year
    • Acquis. month
    • Scrap Value Percent
    • Valid from
    • Valid to
  • Additional Fields - Additional fields or values you want to add to the details. These fields are retrieved dynamically from SAP ECC - RFC.

Outputs :

  • Fixed Asset Data - Fixed asset document details.
  • Status - If the request is executed successfully, Status is set to “Success”. If there is a failure in SAP ECC - RFC, Status is set to “Error”.
  • Error Message - Reason for error as returned from SAP ECC - RFC in the RETURN object. Populated only when an error occurs.

Error Messages :

  • Encountered an error. Check log for more details.

To use this action, the corresponding SAP ECC - RFC connection and credential must be created and associated with the SAP_ECC Connection & Credential alias. Learn More

Note: Requires a subscription for production use. Read More.
sys_hub_action_type_definition.name: Create Fixed Asset
